kfl-stack (0.4.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * kflc gains a --headless mode that emits standalone console and batch
    programs requiring no windowing runtime: a simulation prints its
    observations, a plotting program writes a PNG and an SVG per figure,
    and a compute program prints values from a `run` entry function.
  * New `print` statement writes string literals and numeric expressions
    to standard output.
  * The vehicle model gains a generic payload attachment surface.
  * Corrected the vendored CMINPACK license to the Minpack license and
    reproduced its required University of Chicago / Argonne acknowledgment.
  * Development packages now install only their own headers, making the
    meta-packages co-installable.

 -- Savannah Goring <contact@federatedindustrial.com>  Thu, 02 Jul 2026 15:00:05 +0100

kfl-stack (0.1.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian release.
  * Initial release: kflc (KFL compiler, grammar v3.1) plus the
    portable library suite.
  * Per-library packaging: 37 binary packages (runtime + dev pairs)
    plus three meta-packages (kfl-stack-core, kfl-stack-aux,
    kfl-stack-astro).
  * Fortran-backed libraries (quad, ode, geomag, atmos) declare
    libgfortran5 as runtime dependency via dh_shlibdeps; -dev packages
    declare gfortran for downstream compile.

 -- Savannah Goring <contact@federatedindustrial.com>  Sun, 24 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000
